      "text": "The format is one of a distributed unconference, in which small break-out groups self-assemble at various locations, and discuss the topic at hand. It is distributed because unlike a conventional conference there can be many locations taking part in different parts of the world each connected by a good streaming internet connection. It is an unconference because it is more participative and interactive, with anyone able to suggest and topic to discuss, and the most popular topics taking a space and inviting contributors.",
      "id": "80ed79f40fbb96f6",
      "type": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "text": "The format involves the following elements:\n<UL><LI>\n    Registration for discussion not broadcast</LI><LI>\n    Talks and video provocations</LI><LI>\n    Multiple self assembled breakout discussions</LI><LI>\n    Video summaries of each group discussion</LI><LI>\n    Asynchronous distribution of video summaries</LI><LI>\n    A live mix, a live stream</LI><LI>\n    Multiple documentary remixes\n</LI></UL>",
      "id": "3f2382111c95be7c",
      "type": "html"
